This particular Popeye's has ABSOLUTELY HORRIBLE SERVICE. I was on lunch-break, decided to go to this location. Wait was long, as it ALWAYS is. Started off by ordering a 7 piece cajun sprinkle wing/tots combo, and a 4 pc tender combo. Okay, we get up to the window, I pay, and also have to tell them to give me sauce at the window or they NEVER do. The staff is unfriendly, and just not very good at their jobs. I get told it's a wait, okay... So we pull up. Wait is literally so LONG, they FORGOT my order even existed. I have to go inside the store to tell them I'm still waiting for my order. They just kinda blow it off, one crew member asked me if I wanted a drink. They THROW it together, and hand it to me. No apology. So I rush back to work only to find the order is WRONG (This happens so frequently here, it's usually always something wrong, no sauces, etc. I just go here because it is very close to work) They didn't give me any tots, the wings were plain, no flavor and they gave me the tiniest tenders I have EVER seen. So I call the store, to tell them exactly what was wrong with my order, and how can we fix this. The young lady told me she'd write my name in the books for a full replacement. Okay, awesome! A few days go by, I go in with my initial receipt to claim my order. They dawdle by, then finally a manager (if you could call him that) claims there was nothing written in the book for my incorrect order. I tell him what I told the woman and he claims there is nothing he can do because it is not written in the books. So I got screwed TWICE. Incorrect food, horrific wait time of almost an HOUR, thrown together, terrible service. And then to get it fixed so everyone can move on, they couldn't help me. I have gone here numerous times and every time they get something wrong. (I like to give multiple chances, as I know very well mistakes can happen) This branch has horrible service and needs to be addressed by corp. Why must the customer have to deal with such rude mannered employees who cannot even perform the job they are paid for, and management lacks in any type of category. I suggest you find somewhere else, or another branch. This one has screwed up for the last time with me. I hope Corp can reach out and train these people on how to get an order correct, and how to fix situations like this more appropriately.  I wish I could give this Popeye's negative ten stars. For this happens far too often.
